    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Is this issue ever going anywhere?  This bug still occurs late 2015 when running jupyter notebook on a headless server.   Why does the server need an X11 server to display output on a web page?\n\n[edit]\nI should note for anyone else landing here, the X11 failure seems to only occur in the default configuration of python notebooks.  Adding `%matplotlib inline` as the first line in a python notebook cell will show plots in the webpage without causing an X11 error.  I just wish this were the default Jupyter  behavior.\n"
  },
